*boost-m4-0.4 (18 Mar 2013)

  18 Mar 2013; Nathan Phillip Brink <binki@gentoo.org> +boost-m4-0.4.ebuild,
  -boost-m4-0.3.ebuild:
  Bump to boost-m4-0.4, fixing LDFLAGS=-Wl,--as-needed which was broken in
  boost-m4-0.3. Fixes bug #461748.

  05 Mar 2013; Christoph Junghans <ottxor@gentoo.org> boost-m4-0.3.ebuild:
  added *-macos keywords

  05 Mar 2013; Nathan Phillip Brink <binki@gentoo.org> -boost-m4-0.2.ebuild:
  Drop old boost-m4-0.2.

*boost-m4-0.3 (05 Mar 2013)

  05 Mar 2013; Nathan Phillip Brink <binki@gentoo.org> +boost-m4-0.3.ebuild:
  Bump to boost-m4-0.3 which includes a Mac OSX -rpath LDFLAGS fix for bug
  #460362.

  01 Dec 2012; Ra√∫l Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> boost-m4-0.2.ebuild,
  boost-m4-0.3_pre121130.ebuild:
  Add ~alpha/~ia64/~sparc wrt #442470

*boost-m4-0.3_pre121130 (30 Nov 2012)

  30 Nov 2012; Justin Lecher <jlec@gentoo.org> +boost-m4-0.3_pre121130.ebuild,
  metadata.xml:
  Add latest snapshot; fixes compilation with >gcc-4.6; fixes gold issues,
  #442582

  13 Nov 2012; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> boost-m4-0.2.ebuild:
  Marked ~hppa (bug #442470).

  10 Nov 2012; Anthony G. Basile <blueness@gentoo.org> boost-m4-0.2.ebuild:
  keyword ppc, bug #442470

  10 Jun 2012; Nathan Phillip Brink <binki@gentoo.org> boost-m4-0.2.ebuild:
  Use tarball instead of zipball, reducing DEPENDencies and (hopefully) making
  mgorny happier.

*boost-m4-0.2 (01 Feb 2012)

  01 Feb 2012; Nathan Phillip Brink <binki@gentoo.org> +boost-m4-0.2.ebuild,
  +metadata.xml:
  Add boost-m4-0.2 for bug #352618, an alternate set of boost-detecting m4
  macros.
